  "prompt": "Is T-fal cookware oven safe?",
  "response": "Yes, many T-fal cookware products are oven-safe, but the specifics can vary depending on the product line and materials used. Generally, T-fal cookware with metal handles is safe for oven use up to a certain temperature, commonly around 350\u00b0F (175\u00b0C) to 500\u00b0F (260\u00b0C). However, cookware with plastic or rubberized handles may have lower maximum oven-safe temperatures.\n\nAlways consult the manufacturer's instructions for your specific T-fal cookware to confirm its oven safety and maximum temperature limits. It's important to adhere to these guidelines to prevent damage to your cookware and ensure safe usage.",
